                            <br><br><br>
                                    <p>
                                        The Greater Glider is the largest gliding mammal in Australia, which have creamy white fur on their underside and thick dark grey-brown fur on their back, with large furry ears and a long shaggy tail that is good for grabbing the trunks and branches when they are climbing the trees. There are different morphs of these animals, dark and light-coloured.

                                    </p>
