                             style="line-height: 3; font-family: cursive; font-size: 18px;">
                            <br><br><br>
                                    <p>
                                        The main habitat of Greater Gliders is the east coast of mainland Australia, from central Queesnland to central Victoria. In Victoria, They are usually found in the forests of eastern Victoria, including inland and southern falls of the Great Dividing Range and the Strzelecki and Strathbogie Ranges. They can barely be observed in habitats on high altitude alpine and sub-apline, Wilson’s Promontory and cleared areas, but they are easily found in Daylesford and the surrounding forests excluding Otway Ranges.

                                    </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">

