                            <br><br><br>
                                    <p>
                                        Greater Gliders prefer to use older, hollow-bearing trees in moist forest for shelters and nesting. They like to live in groups, with all the family members living in the trees within the same range. They feed on certain species of young eucalyptus leaves.

                                    </p>
